1
00:00:00,060 --> 00:00:02,460
A week ago, I turned 57.

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:05,520
And if I could go back to
talk to my 20-year-old self

3
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,810
and give him some advice,

4
00:00:06,810 --> 00:00:09,180
here are the 50 things I would say.

5
00:00:09,180 --> 00:00:11,220
Number one, work on your willpower.

6
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:13,290
You'll never reach your full potential

7
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:14,940
or outwork your rivals

8
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:18,150
if you can't focus for
long periods of time.

9
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:20,070
This was true when I was younger,

10
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:21,990
but it's even more applicable now

11
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:25,380
with so many distractions
fighting for your attention.

12
00:00:25,380 --> 00:00:27,150
If you can focus and work hard,

13
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:29,610
you'll be miles ahead of everyone else,

14
00:00:29,610 --> 00:00:33,060
so why not use this video
as a test for yourself?

15
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:35,100
If you can reach the end without skipping

16
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:38,280
and actually listen to
everything I say on a deep level,

17
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:39,840
then you'll be in the minority.

18
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:43,290
Number two, become more of
a producer than a consumer.

19
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:45,900
I understand consuming content is key,

20
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,580
especially if you learn a lot.

21
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,020
However, you should always be trying

22
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:50,520
to put more out into the world

23
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,690
than you're taking,

24
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:54,420
otherwise you'll end up robbed
of your time and attention.

25
00:00:54,420 --> 00:00:56,970
Number three, be nice
to people on the come up

26
00:00:56,970 --> 00:00:59,490
because you never know where
they're gonna be in the future.

27
00:00:59,490 --> 00:01:00,930
There have been countless times

28
00:01:00,930 --> 00:01:03,360
when I've underestimated
someone's potential,

29
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:06,810
only to see them achieve
credible success later on.

30
00:01:06,810 --> 00:01:09,780
By treating everyone with
kindness and support,

31
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:11,790
even if you're unsure about their plans,

32
00:01:11,790 --> 00:01:13,620
you create good karma.

33
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:14,730
If they strike it big,

34
00:01:14,730 --> 00:01:16,980
they'll likely remember those
who were in their corner,

35
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,140
and you may benefit from
that connection too.

36
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:21,780
Number four, watch what
most people are doing

37
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:23,070
and then do the opposite.

38
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:25,170
It took me a few years to find the courage

39
00:01:25,170 --> 00:01:28,238
to leave my nine to five job
and start my own business.

40
00:01:28,238 --> 00:01:31,680
I was comfortable with the
routine of receiving a paycheck

41
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,900
and accepting life as it was.

42
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,730
However, when I built a staircase

43
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:37,030
for a wealthy entrepreneur,

44
00:01:37,030 --> 00:01:40,110
I realized there was
another path available.

45
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:42,390
I'm grateful I took that chance.

46
00:01:42,390 --> 00:01:44,280
I mean, I wouldn't be a millionaire now

47
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,290
if I continued working for someone else.

48
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:48,150
This is a pretty simple idea

49
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,340
because if you do what everyone else does,

50
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:52,200
then you're gonna get the same results.

51
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:55,320
So reject the idea of
being normal and vanilla.

52
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,550
As the saying goes,

53
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,080
if you're everyone's cup of tea,

54
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:58,980
then you're a mug.

55
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:00,870
Number five, who you know

56
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:03,240
matters 1,000 times
more than what you know.

57
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:06,390
A great network beats money
in the bank every time.

58
00:02:06,390 --> 00:02:08,130
I can't count how many times

59
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:09,930
my connections have helped me out.

60
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:12,630
Number six, never talk
behind someone's back.

61
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,460
If you have a problem with someone,

62
00:02:14,460 --> 00:02:17,259
you should address it with
them directly or not at all.

63
00:02:17,259 --> 00:02:19,470
You may think that gossiping about people

64
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:20,400
when they can't hear you

65
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,690
makes you seem cool,

66
00:02:21,690 --> 00:02:24,240
but it actually makes
you seem less trustworthy

67
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,890
to those who are listening,

68
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:28,650
as they'll think you're doing
the same behind their backs.

69
00:02:28,650 --> 00:02:30,720
Number seven, give yourself permission

70
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,310
to make more mistakes.

71
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:35,070
Most of my success has
come from my failures.

72
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:36,780
I wish I knew this sooner.

73
00:02:36,780 --> 00:02:39,030
I mean, I enjoy skiing with my son,

74
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,410
and I remember one year

75
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:43,170
we competed to see who
could fall the least.

76
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:45,870
I won, as Curtis fell over a lot,

77
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:48,060
however he improved tremendously,

78
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:51,210
and now he's a much faster skier than me.

79
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:53,880
This just proves that
failure leads to improvement

80
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:54,900
if it's embraced.

81
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,787
So remember, if you never fail,

82
00:02:56,787 --> 00:02:59,010
then you're probably
not trying hard enough.

83
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:02,070
Number eight, make
reversible decisions quickly.

84
00:03:02,070 --> 00:03:05,197
I actually picked this one up
from Jeff Bezos, as he said,

85
00:03:05,197 --> 00:03:07,267
"With a decision that you can go back on,

86
00:03:07,267 --> 00:03:09,277
"your biggest risk is dragging your feet

87
00:03:09,277 --> 00:03:10,890
"and not making a decision."

88
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:13,350
However, when decisions are irreversible,

89
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:14,446
slow them down

90
00:03:14,446 --> 00:03:17,730
as the biggest risk here is
making the wrong decision,

91
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:20,400
so it's worth getting as
much information as possible

92
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,930
before taking action.

93
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:24,870
Number nine, focus on one thing at a time.

94
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:28,140
The truth is there is no
such thing as multitasking,

95
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:30,120
just multi-failing,

96
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,350
so give yourself time

97
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:34,560
to focus on one thing
deeply without distractions.

98
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,750
Trust me, you'll achieve far more.

99
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:39,390
Number 10, don't be the best,

100
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:40,440
be the only.

101
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:43,710
You can do this by learning
seemingly unrelated skills

102
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:45,600
and combining them together.

103
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,828
Steve Jobs is well known

104
00:03:46,828 --> 00:03:48,060
for mixing his love

105
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:50,790
for calligraphy and design with technology

106
00:03:50,790 --> 00:03:53,190
and creating Apple as we know it today.

107
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:55,470
He was the only person
doing that at the time.

108
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,960
This is one of my golden pieces of advice,

109
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,630
and after every 10 bits of advice,

110
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:01,710
I'm gonna drop another one of these.

111
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:04,890
Number 11, if you don't like
something, then change it.

112
00:04:04,890 --> 00:04:05,754
If you can't change it,

113
00:04:05,754 --> 00:04:08,110
then change your attitude, never complain.

114
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:10,290
I used to be a bit of a complainer,

115
00:04:10,290 --> 00:04:11,490
but as I've gone through life,

116
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:13,920
I've realized that 80% of the time,

117
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,780
no one cares about your problems,

118
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:18,780
and 20% of them wish they
had them in the first place.

119
00:04:18,780 --> 00:04:20,713
Even if your whole world is crumbling,

120
00:04:20,713 --> 00:04:23,940
complaining won't do
anything positive for you.

121
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:26,130
I'm not saying you can't
express your feelings,

122
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:27,900
however it's important to remember

123
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,400
we all have our own problems

124
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,920
and not many people
care about fixing yours.

125
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,650
Number 12, work smart, not hard.

126
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:36,180
As I've grown old and gray,

127
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:39,090
I've seen the birth of lots
of revolutionary technology

128
00:04:39,090 --> 00:04:42,960
like color TVs, the iPhone
and artificial intelligence.

129
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:46,230
The crazy thing is a lot of
my generation aren't like me

130
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:47,550
and choose to reject it,

131
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:49,920
which makes working smart very difficult.

132
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,750
But for you tech savvy youngsters,

133
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:55,080
working smart and building a
business has never been easier.

134
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,240
I mean, take a look at this, for example.

135
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,360
One of the hottest businesses
at the moment is e-Commerce

136
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,010
as it's infinitely scalable

137
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:04,230
and provides geographical freedom,

138
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:07,372
but building a website requires
either a unique skillset

139
00:05:07,372 --> 00:05:10,140
or money to pay somebody
else to do it for you.

140
00:05:10,140 --> 00:05:11,910
But with Build Your Store AI,

141
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:14,250
you can get a fully custom Shopify store

142
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:17,100
built completely for free
in less than two minutes.

143
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,750
Here's one I made earlier.

144
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,583
As you can see,

145
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:22,140
all I had to do was select
the niche of my store,

146
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:23,700
pick some images that worked

147
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:26,580
and then let AI take care of the rest.

148
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:29,639
The website even comes with
winning products and ready pages

149
00:05:29,639 --> 00:05:31,950
like policies and returns.

150
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:34,440
Of course, this is all fully customizable,

151
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,007
but it's a great starting point

152
00:05:36,007 --> 00:05:39,300
and perfectly sums up
working smart and not hard.

153
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:41,070
I'll leave a link in the description below

154
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:43,440
if you're interested in
selling products online

155
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,870
and having a free website built for you.

156
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,490
The link also gives you access

157
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:50,190
to a special Shopify trial for $1

158
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:52,350
so you can launch your business risk free.

159
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:54,870
Number 13, assume you can learn something

160
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:56,340
from everyone you meet.

161
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:57,173
I'm not afraid to admit

162
00:05:57,173 --> 00:06:00,480
that in my 20s I was
a little bit arrogant.

163
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,680
I thought I knew everything,

164
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,700
but, looking back,

165
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:05,375
I now realize how much
more I still had to learn.

166
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:07,671
I'm very aware that in 10 years time,

167
00:06:07,671 --> 00:06:10,020
I'll look back at what I currently know

168
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:11,760
and probably think the same.

169
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:12,900
Even at 57,

170
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,600
I'm still learning new things every day.

171
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,097
So if I were you,

172
00:06:17,097 --> 00:06:18,870
I'd just skip the arrogant stage

173
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:20,700
and be open to learning new things,

174
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,380
even from those younger than you.

175
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:25,230
Number 14, never disrespect your elders.

176
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:27,720
I know on the surface
we might seem boring,

177
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,180
but us older people
have been through a lot.

178
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:33,480
Our experience can probably
help you avoid many mistakes

179
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,160
if you take the time to listen.

180
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,680
However, if you disagree
with something I say,

181
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,480
you don't have to follow my advice.

182
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,270
All I ask is that you
listen with an open mind

183
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:43,980
and then make your own decisions.

184
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:47,430
Number 15, don't be afraid
of change, embrace it.

185
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,860
I started a chain of radio
controlled model shops

186
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:50,910
in my 20s,

187
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,985
and the goal was to
expand all over the world.

188
00:06:52,985 --> 00:06:55,380
However, when the internet was created,

189
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:56,670
that all changed.

190
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:59,370
Suddenly, more and more
people were shopping online

191
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,810
and my shops were suffering.

192
00:07:00,810 --> 00:07:02,070
I could have just given up.

193
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:03,697
However, instead, I embraced the change

194
00:07:03,697 --> 00:07:06,390
and started the e-Commerce
side of my business,

195
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:08,790
and started making more than ever before.

196
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:11,310
There's a famous quote that
sums this up quite well,

197
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,566
and it goes like this.

198
00:07:12,566 --> 00:07:15,330
Once a new technology rolls over you,

199
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:16,972
if you're not part of the steam roller,

200
00:07:16,972 --> 00:07:18,600
you're part of the road.

201
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:21,990
Number 16, live in the
moment, not on your phone.

202
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:24,090
Make the most of every moment.

203
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:27,150
You don't need to capture
everything for social media.

204
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:29,610
Focus on what's happening
right in front of you,

205
00:07:29,610 --> 00:07:30,840
especially when it's something

206
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,880
you might never experience again.

207
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:35,100
I didn't realize how many last times

208
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:36,739
I went through without knowing it,

209
00:07:36,739 --> 00:07:38,820
whether it's hanging
out with your friends,

210
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:41,820
that weekly bowling night
or a yearly tradition.

211
00:07:41,820 --> 00:07:43,913
One day, it'll be the final time,

212
00:07:43,913 --> 00:07:46,230
and you probably won't even see it coming.

213
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:48,930
Number 17, always pay the bill.

214
00:07:48,930 --> 00:07:50,040
This one's for the guys.

215
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,600
Yeah, it might sound a bit old school,

216
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,473
but it's part of being a gentleman.

217
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:57,480
Paying the bill is just a small
gesture that shows you care,

218
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,430
and, no, it's not simping,

219
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:02,040
unless you're always doing
it and getting nothing back.

220
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:05,130
Number 18, say no if you
genuinely aren't ready.

221
00:08:05,130 --> 00:08:07,560
It's okay to admit when you need more time

222
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,143
or aren't quite prepared
to take something on.

223
00:08:10,143 --> 00:08:13,071
Sure, people love to say
fake it 'til you make it,

224
00:08:13,071 --> 00:08:16,260
but if you can't close
that knowledge gap in time,

225
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:17,940
it's smarter to turn it down

226
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:20,040
rather than risk being in over your head.

227
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,960
Number 19, present yourself

228
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,880
in the way you wish to be perceived.

229
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:24,713
It's important to think

230
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:27,180
about how you want to
come across to others

231
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,920
and then make a conscious effort

232
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,750
to present yourself in that way.

233
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:33,600
This includes how you
dress, how you speak,

234
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,490
what you post on social media

235
00:08:35,490 --> 00:08:37,135
and even how you carry yourself.

236
00:08:37,135 --> 00:08:40,440
Think of it like building
your own video game character

237
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,550
from the ground up.

238
00:08:41,550 --> 00:08:44,310
Number 20, mentally prepare yourself

239
00:08:44,310 --> 00:08:45,780
for your loved ones dying.

240
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:48,150
I know this isn't the
nicest thing to talk about,

241
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:49,735
but you do need to think about it.

242
00:08:49,735 --> 00:08:51,840
When something like this happens,

243
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,300
it can send shock waves
throughout our lives.

244
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,370
And if you aren't ready to withstand this,

245
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:57,929
then you'll just crumble.

246
00:08:57,929 --> 00:08:59,400
Thinking this way

247
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,500
also helps you to value every moment

248
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,030
you spend with your loved ones,

249
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:04,500
as nothing is forever.

250
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:07,710
Number 21, never take
rejection personally.

251
00:09:07,710 --> 00:09:09,900
Whether it's a job
interview or something else,

252
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:12,150
try to see things from
their point of view.

253
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:14,370
Use the feedback to improve the next time.

254
00:09:14,370 --> 00:09:15,930
Taking rejection personally

255
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:18,540
just holds you back from
growing and getting better.

256
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:22,560
Number 22, don't be embarrassed
to take a nap now and again.

257
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,600
I know this one may sound silly,

258
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,646
but when I was younger,

259
00:09:25,646 --> 00:09:28,440
I thought naps were for
kids and old people.

260
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,240
But I've met so many millionaires

261
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:33,300
that swear by having short
power naps throughout the day.

262
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:36,510
So don't be ashamed or
embarrassed about taking a nap,

263
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:38,760
as it can actually help
you be more productive

264
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:39,593
in the long run.

265
00:09:39,593 --> 00:09:42,840
Number 23, learn from those
who disagree with you.

266
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:46,410
Too many people are trapped
in a bubble on social media,

267
00:09:46,410 --> 00:09:48,870
and they can't face their
beliefs being challenged.

268
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:51,450
Remember, you can learn
something from everyone,

269
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:54,060
so just because you don't
agree on a couple of things,

270
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:56,610
it doesn't mean you shouldn't
listen to their opinions.

271
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:59,040
Number 24, never be late.

272
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:02,460
Punctuality is a sign of
respect for other people's time,

273
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:05,038
and shows that you're
reliable and trustworthy.

274
00:10:05,038 --> 00:10:09,960
Early is on time, on time is
late and late is unforgivable.

275
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:14,010
Number 25, be motivated by
something greater than money.

276
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:15,720
This comes from your values.

277
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,270
Having strong values means
that no one can buy you,

278
00:10:18,270 --> 00:10:20,024
no matter how much they offer.

279
00:10:20,024 --> 00:10:23,310
These values are principles
you refuse to compromise

280
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,990
under any circumstances.

281
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:27,360
One of mine is prioritizing my family.

282
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,280
If something isn't in their best interest,

283
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,854
then I won't do it
under any circumstances.

284
00:10:31,854 --> 00:10:35,304
So figure out what you're
passionate about and make a stand.

285
00:10:35,304 --> 00:10:38,460
This will allow you to command
more respect from others.

286
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:41,670
Number 26, be fueled by vision, not fear.

287
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:44,520
Fearful people worry about
losing what they have

288
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,290
and can never see far enough ahead

289
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:48,180
to build something for the future.

290
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:51,060
Number 27, stand up to bullies.

291
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:53,220
I stayed stuck in a job way too long,

292
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,870
letting my manager push me around,

293
00:10:54,870 --> 00:10:58,110
before I finally quit and
started my own business.

294
00:10:58,110 --> 00:11:00,180
Trust me, you can't let anyone,

295
00:11:00,180 --> 00:11:02,790
whether it's a man or a woman, bully you.

296
00:11:02,790 --> 00:11:03,720
Most of the time,

297
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,610
if you stand up for yourself once,

298
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:06,780
that's all it takes.

299
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:09,330
Bullies can seriously
mess with your confidence,

300
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:10,800
and that's the last thing you need

301
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,990
when you're young and
trying to find your own way.

302
00:11:12,990 --> 00:11:16,230
Number 28, use your unfair advantages.

303
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:18,900
Everyone has certain
strengths or circumstances

304
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,100
that can give them an edge,

305
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,253
and it's important to
identify and use them.

306
00:11:22,253 --> 00:11:25,710
An unfair advantage is
something that sets you apart,

307
00:11:25,710 --> 00:11:27,480
whether it's a specific skill,

308
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,940
a connection or your life situation.

309
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:31,410
It's not about cheating.

310
00:11:31,410 --> 00:11:33,930
It's about recognizing what
you're naturally good at

311
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:36,720
or the opportunities you
have that others might not,

312
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:39,390
and using those to your
advantage to get ahead.

313
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,820
Number 29, skip the flashy car.

314
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,380
It's a waste in your 20s.

315
00:11:43,380 --> 00:11:45,000
Buy used but reliable.

316
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,910
I've seen so many young people
come into money quickly,

317
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:50,250
only to blow it on things like luxury cars

318
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:51,270
and designer gear.

319
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:54,102
Sure, it's easy to have short
term success and splurge,

320
00:11:54,102 --> 00:11:56,010
but what's far more impressive

321
00:11:56,010 --> 00:11:58,337
is consistently building wealth over time.

322
00:11:58,337 --> 00:12:00,390
That's what true legends do.

323
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:03,510
Number 30, prioritize your reputation.

324
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:06,210
It's one of the few things
that lives on after you die.

325
00:12:06,210 --> 00:12:07,980
I've had the unfortunate experience

326
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:10,197
of attending many funerals in my time,

327
00:12:10,197 --> 00:12:13,470
and the person is always
remembered for their character.

328
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:15,270
In other words, their reputation,

329
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:17,040
not their achievements.

330
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:19,920
Number 31, don't compare
yourself to your friends.

331
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,720
We all have our own path to walk.

332
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:24,120
As long as you're improving
on what you've done before,

333
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,907
then you're going in the right direction.

334
00:12:25,907 --> 00:12:27,870
If you do this for enough years,

335
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:30,577
then you'll look back and be
shocked at how far you've come.

336
00:12:30,577 --> 00:12:33,321
It's all about taking those baby steps

337
00:12:33,321 --> 00:12:36,870
and not getting distracted by
what everyone else is doing.

338
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:40,950
Number 32, don't let a bad
day turn into a bad week.

339
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:42,690
It takes less than five seconds

340
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:44,400
for someone to ruin your day.

341
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,630
And if you're not careful,

342
00:12:45,630 --> 00:12:48,660
that can spiral into a
whole week of negativity.

343
00:12:48,660 --> 00:12:50,370
It's important to let it go

344
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:52,566
so you don't miss out on
all the good opportunities

345
00:12:52,566 --> 00:12:54,900
that that week still has to offer.

346
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:58,140
Number 33, always pay
off your credit card.

347
00:12:58,140 --> 00:13:00,966
I had to mention this one
because it's so important.

348
00:13:00,966 --> 00:13:04,140
If you don't pay off your
credit card in full each month,

349
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:07,170
you're just wasting money and
hurting your credit score.

350
00:13:07,170 --> 00:13:08,610
Be smart about it.

351
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:10,230
Make paying it off a habit,

352
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:11,940
and it'll stick with you for life.

353
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:15,120
Number 34, any job is better than no job.

354
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:18,420
Being out of work can really
take its toll on you mentally,

355
00:13:18,420 --> 00:13:20,010
so if the only position available

356
00:13:20,010 --> 00:13:22,200
is washing cars for $10 an hour,

357
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,033
go for it.

358
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,540
It's not just about the pay.

359
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:25,980
It's about getting out there,

360
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,240
interacting with others

361
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,830
and boosting your self-esteem

362
00:13:28,830 --> 00:13:30,690
that comes from showing up for a job.

363
00:13:30,690 --> 00:13:32,610
Who knows, you might make some mates.

364
00:13:32,610 --> 00:13:33,570
I still have a friend

365
00:13:33,570 --> 00:13:36,900
I met during my car
washing days 47 years ago.

366
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:39,450
Number 35, never buy an investment

367
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:41,340
without doing your own research.

368
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:44,820
I've seen so many people lose
money on poor investments,

369
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:47,280
and usually it's because
they didn't take the time

370
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,210
to look into it.

371
00:13:48,210 --> 00:13:49,599
Make sure you do your homework,

372
00:13:49,599 --> 00:13:52,860
even if you think you might
miss out on something big.

373
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:54,847
If someone is pressuring you to invest,

374
00:13:54,847 --> 00:13:56,790
that's often a red flag.

375
00:13:56,790 --> 00:13:59,700
Number 36, being a great storyteller

376
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:01,380
can get you anything you want.

377
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:04,367
Knowing how to tell a good
story is such a game changer.

378
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:06,360
Whether you're just
hanging out with friends

379
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,970
or trying to impress a
future business partner,

380
00:14:08,970 --> 00:14:11,010
a great story grabs attention,

381
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:12,054
makes your point stick

382
00:14:12,054 --> 00:14:15,390
and helps you connect with
people in a more real way.

383
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:17,970
Plus, it's just a fun way
to get your ideas across

384
00:14:17,970 --> 00:14:19,200
and leave an impression,

385
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,880
no matter the situation.

386
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:23,760
Number 37, don't live
your life for others.

387
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,740
Don't let haters dictate your choices

388
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,466
or make you shy away from
doing what you truly want.

389
00:14:28,466 --> 00:14:31,042
If friends or family are
pushing you into a career

390
00:14:31,042 --> 00:14:32,474
you're not passionate about,

391
00:14:32,474 --> 00:14:35,417
take a moment to think
about your situation.

392
00:14:35,417 --> 00:14:38,190
You don't wanna end up
in a job you despise

393
00:14:38,190 --> 00:14:39,450
for the rest of your life.

394
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:42,630
Focus on building and living
your dream life instead.

395
00:14:42,630 --> 00:14:45,870
Number 38, have a solid paycheck routine.

396
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:49,110
Firstly, use 50% to pay for your needs.

397
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:51,690
This is your food, rent and electricity.

398
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:55,710
Secondly, save 20% in a high
interest savings account.

399
00:14:55,710 --> 00:14:57,540
This is your emergency fund.

400
00:14:57,540 --> 00:15:00,908
Thirdly, use 30% to pay
off any high interest debt.

401
00:15:00,908 --> 00:15:03,810
This is your credit cards and car finance.

402
00:15:03,810 --> 00:15:06,360
Fourth, once you've paid off your debts,

403
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:10,761
use 25% to invest in a Roth
IRA or a stocks and shares ISA.

404
00:15:10,761 --> 00:15:13,060
This is to grow your wealth.

405
00:15:13,060 --> 00:15:17,010
Fifth, put 5% towards some risky place

406
00:15:17,010 --> 00:15:18,698
like starting your own business.

407
00:15:18,698 --> 00:15:21,300
This is your chance to
make some fast money.

408
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,588
Number 39, it's not the end of the world

409
00:15:23,588 --> 00:15:25,860
if you don't have everything figured out.

410
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:28,230
Everyone is winging it to some degree,

411
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:30,731
and it took me over 20
years to realize this.

412
00:15:30,731 --> 00:15:34,230
Most people are just navigating
life as best they can.

413
00:15:34,230 --> 00:15:36,180
I used to think I was at a disadvantage

414
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:39,540
for not attending business
school or even university,

415
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,760
but as I've met more
people over the years,

416
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,890
I've learned that we're
all just doing our best,

417
00:15:43,890 --> 00:15:45,690
learning and failing every day.

418
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:48,090
You'll never reach the point
where you know everything,

419
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:50,160
so it's best to start as soon as you can

420
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,720
and just figure it out as you go.

421
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:55,163
Number 40, retirement might
feel like it will never come,

422
00:15:55,163 --> 00:15:56,430
but it will,

423
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:58,230
start investing for it now.

424
00:15:58,230 --> 00:15:59,520
I know a lot of YouTubers

425
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,975
are saying investing your
money is not worth the time

426
00:16:01,975 --> 00:16:04,256
as you'll only get 8% per year.

427
00:16:04,256 --> 00:16:07,500
However, they aren't looking
at the bigger picture.

428
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:10,320
Of course, it's important
to make money quickly,

429
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,730
but it's equally as important

430
00:16:11,730 --> 00:16:14,400
to let some of it grow
passively for your retirement.

431
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,644
Number 41, the quality of your questions

432
00:16:16,644 --> 00:16:19,020
will shape your future success.

433
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:21,330
I receive a lot of DMs.

434
00:16:21,330 --> 00:16:23,910
And while I try to respond
to as many as possible,

435
00:16:23,910 --> 00:16:27,240
I often have to sift through
them to find the valuable ones.

436
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,235
I assume this is the same
for most successful people.

437
00:16:30,235 --> 00:16:32,887
For instance, if your message starts with,

438
00:16:32,887 --> 00:16:34,387
"Hi, I know you're busy,

439
00:16:34,387 --> 00:16:36,360
"but can I ask a question?"

440
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,980
You've already missed your chance.

441
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:39,067
Another common one is,

442
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:40,740
"Hi, can we have a chat?"

443
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:42,450
That won't get you far either.

444
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:45,120
Instead, take some time to
think about your question

445
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,830
and craft it thoughtfully.

446
00:16:46,830 --> 00:16:47,820
When you do that,

447
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:50,730
you're much more likely to
receive a meaningful answer.

448
00:16:50,730 --> 00:16:53,190
Remember, the quality of your question

449
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:56,400
will directly impact the
value of the response you get.

450
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:59,160
Number 42, make sure to enjoy the journey,

451
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,260
not just focus on the destination.

452
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:02,617
There's a saying I've lived by,

453
00:17:02,617 --> 00:17:04,267
"Happiness is a journey,

454
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:05,616
"not a destination."

455
00:17:05,616 --> 00:17:07,140
What that really means

456
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:09,420
is that the ups and
downs of a great journey

457
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:11,010
stay with you forever,

458
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:13,440
while the destination
is just a brief moment

459
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,880
that quickly fades away.

460
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,550
Think about all those athletes
you see getting interviewed

461
00:17:17,550 --> 00:17:19,950
after winning a gold medal or a big race.

462
00:17:19,950 --> 00:17:21,007
They're always asked,

463
00:17:21,007 --> 00:17:22,410
"How does it feel?"

464
00:17:22,410 --> 00:17:24,097
And almost everyone says,

465
00:17:24,097 --> 00:17:25,608
"It hasn't sunk in yet."

466
00:17:25,608 --> 00:17:28,770
I think that's because they
feel a bit of emptiness

467
00:17:28,770 --> 00:17:30,420
after reaching their goal.

468
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:32,730
Sure, they've accomplished
something amazing,

469
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:34,885
but then it's like what's next?

470
00:17:34,885 --> 00:17:38,610
So savor the ride and all the
experiences along the way.

471
00:17:38,610 --> 00:17:41,307
Number 43, nothing is ever free.

472
00:17:41,307 --> 00:17:43,080
If you're not spending money,

473
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,490
then you're spending time.

474
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:45,630
From an early age,

475
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:46,463
I always told my son

476
00:17:46,463 --> 00:17:49,380
that nothing in his world
comes without a cost.

477
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:50,460
If you want something,

478
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:52,530
then you need to earn money to buy it.

479
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:53,940
He would often argue with me

480
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:56,220
about things he saw advertised as free,

481
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:57,810
and I'd explain those offers

482
00:17:57,810 --> 00:17:59,820
often end up costing you the most.

483
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:01,933
That's because if something
isn't costing you money,

484
00:18:01,933 --> 00:18:03,911
it's likely costing you your time.

485
00:18:03,911 --> 00:18:07,260
You've probably heard
the saying time is money,

486
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:08,798
and it couldn't be more accurate.

487
00:18:08,798 --> 00:18:09,900
When you're young,

488
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,391
you tend to think you have
all the time in the world,

489
00:18:12,391 --> 00:18:14,640
but you don't always value it enough.

490
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,890
Don't waste it because before you know it

491
00:18:16,890 --> 00:18:20,400
you'll be 57 reflecting on
your twilight years to come.

492
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:23,520
Number 44, stop waiting to be inspired

493
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:24,600
and just get on with it.

494
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:27,402
Inspiration can be pretty
hard to come by sometimes,

495
00:18:27,402 --> 00:18:30,300
but sitting around waiting
for that ah-ha moment

496
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:32,070
can really slow you down.

497
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:34,500
Instead, just start
taking some small steps

498
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:35,910
towards what you want to do.

499
00:18:35,910 --> 00:18:37,110
You might be surprised,

500
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,100
once you dive in,

501
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,980
that motivation can kick
in and make things flow,

502
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:42,291
so don't overthink it.

503
00:18:42,291 --> 00:18:44,850
Just get going and see what happens.

504
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:48,960
Number 45, work hard now
for an easier life later.

505
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:51,232
Take it easy now and
face the consequences.

506
00:18:51,232 --> 00:18:54,272
Life often feels like
it's turned upside down.

507
00:18:54,272 --> 00:18:55,470
When you're young,

508
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:57,743
all you wanna do is party,
travel and have fun,

509
00:18:57,743 --> 00:19:00,677
but you usually lack the funds to do so.

510
00:19:00,677 --> 00:19:02,550
Then as you get older,

511
00:19:02,550 --> 00:19:05,310
your priorities shift
towards wanting security,

512
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,080
stability and enough money

513
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,030
to enjoy a comfortable retirement.

514
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:10,980
You may eventually achieve that,

515
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:13,650
but it often comes after
years of hard work,

516
00:19:13,650 --> 00:19:16,740
pushing yourself until retirement at 67

517
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:19,740
and sometimes not living long
enough to enjoy it fully.

518
00:19:19,740 --> 00:19:21,570
If you put in the effort in your 20s

519
00:19:21,570 --> 00:19:24,120
and resist the urge to
follow the usual path,

520
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,580
you can lay a solid financial foundation.

521
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:28,590
This way, starting in your 30s,

522
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:30,083
life can become a lot easier.

523
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:31,380
I did just that,

524
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:33,390
and it's been an amazing journey.

525
00:19:33,390 --> 00:19:37,140
Number 46, tackle the
tough tasks in the morning.

526
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:39,300
- [Crew Member] He says when
he's filming at five PM.

527
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:40,770
- Well, it's been a long day,

528
00:19:40,770 --> 00:19:41,850
but I enjoy it.

529
00:19:41,850 --> 00:19:44,318
I'm a big believer in making to-do lists,

530
00:19:44,318 --> 00:19:47,059
but I used to approach them all wrong.

531
00:19:47,059 --> 00:19:49,020
I thought it was about checking off

532
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:51,000
as many items as possible,

533
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,949
which often meant I'd do
all the easy tasks first.

534
00:19:53,949 --> 00:19:56,250
While this might have looked impressive,

535
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,200
it left the harder jobs lingering.

536
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,093
Years ago, I shifted my strategy

537
00:20:00,093 --> 00:20:02,369
to prioritize the difficult tasks

538
00:20:02,369 --> 00:20:04,218
first thing in the morning.

539
00:20:04,218 --> 00:20:07,620
This way, I knocked them out
when I was most productive,

540
00:20:07,620 --> 00:20:08,700
and the best part

541
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:11,730
is that once those two or
three tough jobs are done,

542
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:13,920
finishing off the easier
ones in the afternoon

543
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,090
becomes a breeze.

544
00:20:15,090 --> 00:20:17,714
Number 47, the name of a university

545
00:20:17,714 --> 00:20:20,220
means absolutely nothing.

546
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:22,950
Seriously, don't stress
over what uni you go to

547
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:25,461
or rack up debt just for a fancy name.

548
00:20:25,461 --> 00:20:26,618
At the end of the day,

549
00:20:26,618 --> 00:20:29,792
it's what you learn and how you
apply it that really counts.

550
00:20:29,792 --> 00:20:32,880
Employers care more about
skills and experience

551
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:35,790
than the university you may
or may not have attended.

552
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:38,220
Number 48, look after your back.

553
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:41,040
If you slouch, you'll have
issues in your mid-30s.

554
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:44,800
Sadly, this is advice that
comes from firsthand experience.

555
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,860
Your back is crucial.

556
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:50,460
Over time, a bad back can
severely impact your productivity

557
00:20:50,460 --> 00:20:52,752
since it makes it hard
to get anything done.

558
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:54,780
It's similar to having tooth ache,

559
00:20:54,780 --> 00:20:58,470
but, unlike dental pain, there's
no quick fix to relieve it.

560
00:20:58,470 --> 00:21:00,180
This generation benefits greatly

561
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:02,010
from technology and the internet,

562
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:05,160
but it also faces issues
from hunching over keyboards

563
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,110
and lounging on uncomfortable sofas.

564
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:08,850
Prioritize your back health.

565
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:10,950
You'll need it for your entire life.

566
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:12,238
You can replace your teeth,

567
00:21:12,238 --> 00:21:13,980
but you can't get a new back.

568
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:17,160
Number 49, don't stress
about being different.

569
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:18,600
You don't have to fit in.

570
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,780
Honestly, I never let the
idea of being weird bother me.

571
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:22,786
I embraced it.

572
00:21:22,786 --> 00:21:26,368
I was a tall, skinny,
ginger-haired, dyslexic teenager

573
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,040
who loved playing with model airplanes.

574
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,210
Pretty unique, right?

575
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:32,130
When you accept what makes you different,

576
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:33,900
you actually gain an advantage

577
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:36,570
because you become
comfortable with who you are

578
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:37,860
while everyone else is busy

579
00:21:37,860 --> 00:21:40,410
trying to fit into molds
that don't suit them.

580
00:21:40,410 --> 00:21:43,260
My dyslexia has become a superpower,

581
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:45,242
allowing me to solve problems quickly.

582
00:21:45,242 --> 00:21:48,420
Being skinny keeps me relatively fit.

583
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:51,660
My passion for model planes
sparked my first business,

584
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:54,930
and being tall helps me
stand out and be remembered.

585
00:21:54,930 --> 00:21:56,460
As for the ginger hair,

586
00:21:56,460 --> 00:21:57,930
thank goodness that's gone.

587
00:21:57,930 --> 00:22:00,930
Number 50, choose your partner wisely.

588
00:22:00,930 --> 00:22:02,430
I wouldn't be a millionaire today

589
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,040
without my supportive wife.

590
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:06,690
A lot of people get caught up in dating

591
00:22:06,690 --> 00:22:08,250
lots of different options,

592
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:10,200
but, honestly, what really counts

593
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,820
is having a deep connection

594
00:22:11,820 --> 00:22:13,980
and being on the same path together.

595
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:16,140
When you find someone you
think you could marry,

596
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:18,877
make sure you really want to
spend your life with them.

597
00:22:18,877 --> 00:22:20,784
Too many people end up with regrets

598
00:22:20,784 --> 00:22:24,405
because they were blinded
by that early puppy love.

599
00:22:24,405 --> 00:22:27,540
A solid partnership can
make a huge difference,

600
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:28,560
so take your time

601
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:31,800
and choose someone who you
can build a solid future with.

